\f0\b\fs52 \cf0 Coeur a la Creme with Raspberry and Grand Marnier Sauce
\f1\b0\fs32 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\ql\qnatural

\b \cf2 Serves: 
\b0 \cf0 6 to 8 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs40 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs38 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}12 ounces {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cream-cheese/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cream cheese}}, at room temperature\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/4 cup confectioners' sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 1/2 cups cold heavy cream\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons pure {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/extracts/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 vanilla extract}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 teaspoon grated lemon zest\
{\listtext	\'95	}Seeds scraped from 1 vanilla bean\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	\'95	}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/raspberry/index.html"}}{\fldrslt Raspberry}}\cf0  and Grand Marnier Sauce, recipe follows\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 half-pints fresh raspberries\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs40 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs38 \cf0 Place the cream cheese and confectioners' sugar in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment and beat on high speed for 2 minutes. Scrape down the beater and bowl with a rubber spatula and change the beater for the whisk attachment. With the mixer on low speed, add the heavy cream, vanilla, lemon zest, and vanilla bean seeds and beat on high speed until the mixture is very thick, like {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cream/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 whipped cream}}.\
Line a 7-inch sieve with cheesecloth or paper towels so the ends drape over the sides and suspend it over a bowl, making sure that there is space between the bottom of the sieve and the bottom of the bowl for the liquid to drain. Pour the cream mixture into the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cheesecloth/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cheesecloth}}, fold the ends over the top, and refrigerate overnight.\
To serve, discard the liquid, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/unmold/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 unmold}} the cream onto a plate, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/drizzle/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 drizzle}} Raspberry and Grand Marnier Sauce around the base. Serve with raspberries and extra sauce.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs40 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs38 \cf0 Raspberry and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/grand-marnier/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Grand Marnier}} Sauce:\
1 half-pint fresh raspberries\
1/2 cup sugar\
1 cup seedless raspberry jam\
2 tablespoons orange-flavored {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/liqueur/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 liqueur}} (recommended: Grand Marnier)\
Place raspberries, sugar, and 1/4 cup water in a small {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/saucepan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 saucepan}}. Bring to a boil, lower the heat, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/simmer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simmer}} for 4 minutes. Pour the cooked raspberries, the jam, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/orange/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 orange}} liqueur into the bowl of a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/food-processor/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 food processor}} fitted with the steel blade and process until smooth. Chill.\
Yield: 2 cups\
